   {:e #blake3 "9d43f4268d06696ac25943414316da0eea1af08bc8d66ed1e6c76842927209b0" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "CCE-TEST IMPLEMENTER NOTES (addendum to t-1eb0b302): COSINE THRESHOLD CALIBRATION. Tests 14-15 assume cosine > 0.7 for similar texts and < 0.3 for dissimilar. These thresholds DEPEND ON THE SPECIFIC EMBEDDING MODEL (potion-128M). The implementer MUST: (1) Run the actual model on the test strings ('event sourcing' vs 'event replay', 'event sourcing' vs 'SQL injection') FIRST. (2) Record the actual cosine values. (3) Set test thresholds at actual_value ± 0.1 (generous margin). (4) Add a comment in each test: '// Calibrated against potion-128M: actual cosine = X.XX, threshold set at X.XX.' (5) If the model produces unexpected values (e.g., similar texts < 0.5), this is a MODEL QUALITY signal — consider upgrading to MiniLM-L6-v2 (384-dim, quality tier from frankensearch). (6) The JOIN_THRESHOLD in concept.rs (0.65) must also be calibrated against the model. It should be set at: (mean_within_cluster_similarity + mean_between_cluster_similarity) / 2. Run a calibration test: 10 observations from 3 clusters (event-sourcing, error-handling, CLI-structure), compute within-cluster and between-cluster means, set threshold at the midpoint. (7) ALPHA for surprise weighting (2.0 in CCE-2b) is an initial estimate. The calibration loop (OBSERVER-4) will tune it empirically. For now, add a policy manifest attribute :policy/surprise-alpha with default 2.0.; CCE-1 IMPLEMENTER NOTES (addendum to t-23ec839a): (1) DEPENDENCY CRATE: Use model2vec crate directly (not frankensearch-embed — we need only the embedding, not the full search engine). Specifically: the model2vec Rust crate (if it exists) or the safetensors crate + manual vocabulary lookup. Check crates.io for 'model2vec' first. If no Rust crate exists, implement the static embedding manually: it's vocabulary lookup (token → 256-dim vector from safetensors) + mean-pool (average all token vectors). This is ~50 LOC. The safetensors crate (safetensors = '0.4') can read the model file. (2) MODEL FILE DISTRIBUTION: The potion-128m.safetensors file (~5MB) should be downloaded on first use, NOT bundled in the binary. At first embed_text() call: check .braid/.cache/potion-128m.safetensors. If missing, log a one-time message: 'downloading embedding model (5MB)...' and fetch from HuggingFace. If offline, return None (fallback to Jaccard). Store the URL in the policy manifest as :policy/embedding-model-url. (3) TOKENIZER: potion-128M uses a wordpiece tokenizer. The tokenizer.json file must also be downloaded alongside the safetensors file (~500KB). (4) FALLBACK CHAIN: embed_text() should have a clear fallback chain: model available → 256-dim embedding → cosine similarity. Model unavailable → return None → connections.rs falls back to Jaccard. No panic path.; Session entity: :recon/trace-ddfee58785c74b9a; Session entity: :recon/trace-dbe5f6f90cd96160; Session entity: :task/t-de340d95; CCE-4 IMPLEMENTER NOTES (addendum to t-e5dc085e): ENTITY MATCHING RULES — precise specification. (1) PACKAGE ENTITIES: Bootstrap creates entities like :pkg/internal-materialize with :pkg/path = 'internal/materialize'. For matching: extract the LAST path segment (after final /) as the match name. 'internal/materialize' → match name 'materialize'. For the observation text, scan for this match name case-insensitively. (2) MINIMUM MATCH LENGTH: Only match names >= 5 characters to avoid false positives from common words. Packages with short names (e.g., 'cli', 'llm', 'diff') require the FULL path to match (e.g., 'internal/cli' must appear in the text). (3) WORD BOUNDARY: Match name must appear at a word boundary in the observation text. 'materialize' matches in 'the materialize engine' but NOT in 'dematerialized'. Use regex: \\b{match_name}\\b or equivalent character-class check. (4) SPEC ID MATCHING: Spec IDs like 'APP-INV-019', 'INV-MERGE-001' are matched case-insensitively. These are always long enough (>5 chars) and distinctive enough to match without word-boundary requirements. (5) CONCEPT NAME MATCHING: Concept names (e.g., 'event-processing', 'error-handling') are matched with hyphens treated as word separators. 'error handling' and 'error-handling' both match :concept/error-handling. (6) PRIORITY ORDER: If multiple entities match, create links to ALL of them. An observation mentioning 'materialize' and 'events' should link to both :pkg/internal-materialize and :pkg/internal-events. (7) PERFORMANCE: Pre-compute the match table (entity → match_name) at observe time by scanning the store's entity_index once. Cache it in the LiveStore if called frequently. Expected: <5ms for stores with <1000 entities.; CCE-5 IMPLEMENTER NOTES (addendum to t-455bbfa1): FALLBACK BEHAVIORS for steering responses. (1) ZERO CONCEPTS (fresh store, first observation): Response is innate-schema-based. 'This observation relates to [components/dependencies/invariants/patterns/anomalies] (innate schema). 0 concepts formed yet. Explore more to discover patterns.' The innate schema match is via embedding cosine against innate concept centroids. (2) ONE CONCEPT (early exploration): No inter-concept steering question possible. Use intra-concept question: 'concept:X has {N} members spanning {packages}. What about {mentioned_entity} isn't covered yet?' Or coverage-based: '{M} of {T} packages explored. Nearest unexplored: {frontier}.' (3) MULTIPLE CONCEPTS: Full steering mode. Concept membership + structural gap + inter-concept question. (4) INNATE SCHEMA FADE: After 10+ observations, if at least 3 emergent concepts exist, stop showing innate schemas in status. Replace with emergent concept inventory. Innate concepts remain in the store (never deleted — C1) but are filtered from the display by checking :concept/innate = true AND emergent_concept_count >= 3. (5) CONCEPT CORRECTION: If agent observes 'this is about error handling, not event processing' after a wrong assignment, the observe pipeline should detect negation patterns ('not X', 'actually Y', 'wrong concept') and treat as a concept reassignment signal. Implementation: check if observation text contains 'not :concept/' or 'actually :concept/' patterns. If detected: retract the :exploration/concept Ref from the wrong concept, assert Ref to the correct concept, update both centroids. This teaches braid to refine boundaries from agent feedback — the ACCOMMODATION step in Piaget's cycle. (6) SURPRISE IN RESPONSE: Per CCE-2b, include surprise magnitude in the response. Low (<0.1): 'Confirms concept:X'. Medium (0.1-0.3): 'Extends concept:X (surprise=0.XX)'. High (>0.3): 'At the edge of concept:X (surprise=0.XX). This may bridge to concept:Y.' This maps exactly to Piaget: assimilation (low surprise), accommodation (high surprise).; Session entity: :task/t-54551501; Session entity: :recon/trace-11a753095449b1f7; Session entity: :recon/trace-c373dca5c0d67aea; Session entity: :task/t-b733007e" :op :assert}
